    "title": "Can a WebAssembly program leak memory?",
    "body": "<p>WebAssembly programs start with a fixed amount of virtual memory, and can <a href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/design/blob/master/Semantics.md#resizing\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">request additional memory at runtime</a>. They are also encouraged to <a href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/design/blob/master/Semantics.md#resizing\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">discard unused physical pages</a>. Can long running, badly behaved WebAssembly programs <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Memory_leak\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">leak memory</a>? Will this eventually cause the WebAssembly program to crash?</p>\n"
}